TITLE: Constructing Bool Query with Multiple Terms in Elasticsearch
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a bool query that must match three terms for 'name' field with values x, y, and z, while excluding documents where name equals 'a'. Uses the term query for exact matches and combines them using bool query's must and must_not clauses.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/tests/Tests/_VerifySnapshots/QueryOperatorSerializationTests.SearchQueryMixAndMatch_SerializesCorrectly.verified.txt#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  query: {
    bool: {
      must: [
        {
          term: {
            name: {
              value: x
            }
          }
        },
        {
          term: {
            name: {
              value: y
            }
          }
        },
        {
          term: {
            name: {
              value: z
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      must_not: {
        term: {
          name: {
            value: a
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

