TITLE: Consuming Sub-Aggregation Response in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to consume the response from a sub-aggregation. It iterates through the buckets of the 'firstnames' terms aggregation, retrieves the average age for each bucket, and prints the results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/reference/aggregations.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var firstnames = response.Aggregations!.GetStringTerms("firstnames")!;
foreach (var bucket in firstnames.Buckets)
{
	var avg = bucket.Aggregations.GetAverage("avg_age")!;
	Console.WriteLine($"The average age for persons named '{bucket.Key}' is {avg}");
}
```

