TITLE: Configuring Mappings During Index Creation in Elasticsearch with C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create an index with custom mappings using the Elasticsearch .NET client. It sets up mappings for a 'Person' type, defining 'Age' as an integer and 'FirstName' as a non-indexed keyword field.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/reference/mappings.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
await client.Indices.CreateAsync<Person>(index => index
	.Index("index")
	.Mappings(mappings => mappings
		.Properties(properties => properties
			.IntegerNumber(x => x.Age!)
			.Keyword(x => x.FirstName!, keyword => keyword.Index(false))
		)
	)
);
```

