TITLE: Connecting to a Single Elasticsearch Node with Certificate Validation
DESCRIPTION: Creates an ElasticsearchClient instance that connects to a single Elasticsearch node with HTTPS and certificate fingerprint validation. This example uses basic authentication with username and password credentials.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/reference/connecting.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using Elastic.Clients.Elasticsearch;
using Elastic.Transport;

var settings = new ElasticsearchClientSettings(new Uri("https://localhost:9200"))
    .CertificateFingerprint("<FINGERPRINT>")
    .Authentication(new BasicAuthentication("<USERNAME>", "<PASSWORD>"));

var client = new ElasticsearchClient(settings);
```

