TITLE: Connecting to Multiple Elasticsearch Nodes with StaticNodePool
DESCRIPTION: Creates an ElasticsearchClient that connects to multiple Elasticsearch nodes using a StaticNodePool for resiliency. This configuration cycles through nodes in round-robin fashion and avoids unhealthy nodes, using API key authentication.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/reference/connecting.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using Elastic.Clients.Elasticsearch;
using Elastic.Transport;

var nodes = new Uri[]
{
	new Uri("https://myserver1:9200"),
	new Uri("https://myserver2:9200"),
	new Uri("https://myserver3:9200")
};

var pool = new StaticNodePool(nodes);

var settings = new ElasticsearchClientSettings(pool)
    .CertificateFingerprint("<FINGERPRINT>")
    .Authentication(new ApiKey("<API_KEY>"));

var client = new ElasticsearchClient(settings);
```

