TITLE: Executing Top-Level Aggregation using Fluent API in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to perform a top-level aggregation using the Fluent API. It searches the 'persons' index, applies a match all query, and adds a max aggregation on the 'Age' field.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/reference/aggregations.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var response = await client
	.SearchAsync<Person>(search => search
		.Index("persons")
		.Query(query => query
			.MatchAll(_ => {})
		)
		.Aggregations(aggregations => aggregations
			.Add("agg_name", aggregation => aggregation
				.Max(max => max
					.Field(x => x.Age)
				)
			)
		)
		.Size(10)
	);
```

