TITLE: Specifying Sort Order for Aggregations in Elasticsearch .NET Client 9.0
DESCRIPTION: Shows the improved syntax for specifying sort order in aggregations, demonstrating both 8.x and 9.0 approaches.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/blob/main/docs/release-notes/index.md#2025-04-16_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
new SearchRequestDescriptor<Person>()
    .Aggregations(aggs => aggs
        .Add("my_terms", agg => agg
            .Terms(terms => terms
                // 8.x syntax.
                .Order(new List<KeyValuePair<Field, SortOrder>>
                {
                    new KeyValuePair<Field, SortOrder>("_key", SortOrder.Desc)
                })
                // 9.0 fluent syntax.
                .Order(x => x
                    .Add(x => x.Age, SortOrder.Asc)
                    .Add("_key", SortOrder.Desc)
                )
                // 9.0 fluent add syntax (valid for all dictionary-like values).
                .AddOrder("_key", SortOrder.Desc)
            )
        )
    );
```

